%3E%3C%2Ffigcaption%3E%3C%2Ffigure%3E%3Cul%3E%5Cn%3Cli%3EUS%20intelligence%20believes%20Ukraine%20won't%20reach%20the%20key%20city%20of%20Melitopol%2C%20The%20Washington%20Post%20reported.%3C%2Fli%3E%5Cn%3Cli%3EMelitopol%20is%20a%20strategic%20hub%20that%20allows%20Russia%20to%20control%20occupied%20areas%20of%20southern%20Ukraine.%C2%A0%3C%2Fli%3E%5Cn%3Cli%3ERetaking%20the%20city%20is%20a%20landmark%20goal%20for%20Ukraine's%20counteroffensive.%3C%2Fli%3E%5Cn%3C%2Ful%3E%3Cp%3EUS%20intelligence%20officials%20don't%20think%20Ukrainian%20forces%20can%20reach%20the%20strategic%20southeastern%20city%20of%20Melitopol%2C%20believing%20that%20one%20of%20the%20key%20goals%20of%20the%20counteroffensive%20is%20going%20to%20fail%2C%20%3Ca%20rel%3D%5C%22noopener%5C%22%20href%3D%5C%22https%3A%2F%2Fwww.washingtonpost.com%2Fnational-security%2F2023%2F08%2F17%2Fukraine-counteroffensive-melitopol%2F%5C%22%20target%3D%5C%22_blank%5C%22%3EThe%20Washington%20Post%20reported%3C%2Fa%3E.%C2%A0%3C%2Fp%3E%3Cp%3EThis%20is%20according%20to%20unnamed%20people%20from%20within%20the%20intelligence%20community%20who%20were%20familiar%20with%20a%20classified%20forecast%2C%20who%20spoke%20to%20the%20Post.%20Insider%20was%20unable%20to%20independently%20verify%20the%20report.%3C%2Fp%3E%3Cp%3EThe%20assessment%2C%20per%20the%20paper%2C%20is%20based%20on%20Russia's%20massive%20defensive%20preparations%2C%20which%20involve%20hundreds%20of%20miles%20of%20minefields%20and%20trench%20networks%20to%20thwart%20Ukraine's%20advances.%3C%2Fp%3E%3Cp%3ERepublicans%20and%20Democrats%20have%20been%20briefed%20on%20the%20contents%20of%20the%20assessment%2C%20prompting%20recriminations%20from%20both%20those%20who%20have%20criticized%20the%20extent%20of%20US%20military%20support%20and%20those%20who%20called%20for%20more%2C%20the%20paper%20reported.%3C%2Fp%3E%3Cp%3EPatrick%20Bury%2C%20a%20senior%20lecturer%20in%20security%20at%20the%20UK's%20Bath%20University%2C%20told%20Insider%20that%20the%20reported%20assessment%20is%20one%20he%20shares.%3C%2Fp%3E%3Cp%3EA%20breakthrough%2C%20albeit%20with%20changed%20tactics%2C%20is%20not%20out%20of%20the%20realms%20of%20possibility%2C%20Bury%20said.%20%26quot%3BBut%20the%20longer%20we%20stay%20in%20this%20kind%20of%20thing%2C%20the%20chances%20of%20a%20knockout%20blow%20become%20more%20remote.%26quot%3B%3C%2Fp%3E%3Cp%3E%26quot%3BIt%20doesn't%20mean%20they're%20not%20going%20to%20get%20somewhere%2C%20but%20obviously%20time%20is%20ticking%20away%2C%26quot%3B%20he%20added.%20%26quot%3BAnd%20at%20what%20point%20does%20it%20just%20become%20clear%20that%20it's%20not%20working%3F%26quot%3B%3C%2Fp%3E%3Cp%3E%3Ca%20href%3D%5C%22https%3A%2F%2Fwww.businessinsider.com%2Fukraine-melitopol-russia-installed-mayor-says-start-broadcasting-russian-tv-2022-3%3Fr%3DUS%26IR%3DT%5C%22%3EMelitopol%20was%20one%20of%20the%20first%20cities%20to%20fall%20under%20Russian%20control%3C%2Fa%3E%20during%20the%20full-scale%20invasion%20that%20started%20in%20February%202022%2C%20and%20it%20is%20now%20a%20key%20objective%20in%20the%20counteroffensive.%3C%2Fp%3E%3Cp%3EThe%20city%20sits%20almost%20at%20the%20center%20of%20a%20wide%20swathe%20of%20land%20in%20occupied%20southern%20Ukraine%2C%20much%20of%20which%20is%20bordered%20by%20the%20Azov%20Sea%20to%20the%20south%20and%20the%20Dnipro%20River%20to%20the%20north.%3C%2Fp%3E%3Cp%3EMelitopol%20is%20also%20the%20meeting%20place%20for%20a%20web%20of%20captured%20roads%20and%20railway%20lines%20through%20which%20Russia%20transports%20troops%20and%20supplies%20to%20the%20front%20lines%20from%20Crimea%2C%20which%20in%20turn%20is%20connected%20to%20Russia%20via%20the%20Kerch%20Bridge.%3C%2Fp%3E%3Cp%3E%3Ca%20href%3D%5C%22https%3A%2F%2Fwww.businessinsider.com%2Fcrimea-shaping-up-to-be-battleground-that-will-decide-russia-ukraine-war-2023-1%3Fr%3DUS%26IR%3DT%5C%22%3EReaching%20and%20even%20retaking%20Crimea%3C%2Fa%3E%20is%20a%20hallowed%20objective%20in%20Ukraine's%20counteroffensive%2C%20with%20the%20peninsula%20under%20Russian%20occupati