ent%20and%20sniffer%20dogs%20were%20pressed%20into%20service%20by%20the%20CISF%20while%20passengers'%20luggage%20was%20sent%20for%20re-check%2C%20they%20added.%3C%2Fp%3E%5Cn%3Cp%3EThe%20airlines%20said%20it%20was%20cooperating%20with%20the%20security%20agencies.%3C%2Fp%3E%5Cn%3Cp%3E%26quot%3BWe%20confirm%20that%20the%20flight%20UK971%2C%20scheduled%20to%20fly%20from%20Delhi%20to%20Pune%20on%2018%20August%202023%2C%20is%20delayed%20due%20to%20mandatory%20security%20checks%2C%26quot%3B%20it%20said.%3C%2Fp%3E%5Cn%3Cp%3E%26quot%3BIn%20the%20meanwhile%2C%20we%20are%20making%20all%20efforts%20to%20minimise%20inconvenience%20to%20our%20customers%2C%20including%20offering%20them%20refreshments%2C%26quot%3B%20it%20said.%3C%2Fp%3E%3Cp%3E%3Ci%3E(Except%20for%20the%20headline%2C%20this%20story%20has%20not%20been%20edited%20by%20NDTV%20staff%20and%20is%20published%20from%20a%20syndicated%20feed.)%3C%2Fi%3E%3C%2Fp%3E%22%2C%22published%22%3A1692362760000%2C%22visual%22%3A%22https%3A%2F%2Fi.ndtvimg.com%2Fi%2F2016-04%2Fvistara-650_650x400_41460648231.jpg%22%2C%22originID%22%3A%22https%3A%2F%2Fwww.ndtv.com%2Findia-news%2Fvistara-flight-delayed-for-8-hours-at-delhi-airport-over-3-bombs-call-4309194%22%2C%22summary%22%3A%22A%20Delhi-Pune%20Vistara%20airlines%20flight%20was%20delayed%20for%20around%20eight%20hours%20at%20the%20IGI%20Airport%20here%20after%20a%20bomb%20threat%20call%20which%20later%20turned%20out%20to%20be%20hoax%2C%20security%20sources%20and%20police%20said.%22%2C%22author%22%3A%22%22%2C%22engagement%22%3A0%2C%22canonicalUrl%22%3A%22https%3A%2F%2Fwww.ndtv.com%2Findia-news%2Fvistara-flight-delayed-for-8-hours-at-delhi-airport-over-3-bombs-call-4309194%22%2C%22cdnAmpUrl%22%3A%22https%3A%2F%2Fwww-ndtv-com.cdn.ampproject.org%2Fc%2Fs%2Fwww.ndtv.com%2Findia-news%2Fvistara-flight-delayed-for-8-hours-at-delhi-airport-over-3-bombs-call-4309194%2Famp%2F1%22%2C%22ampUrl%22%3A%22https%3A%2F%2Fwww.ndtv.com%2Findia-news%2Fvistara-flight-delayed-for-8-hours-at-delhi-airport-over-3-bombs-call-4309194%2Famp%2F1%22%7D%2C%7B%22title%22%3A%22'Who%20Will%20Move%20First%3F'%3A%20Is%20a%20Modi-Xi%20Meeting%20on%20the%20Cards%20at%20Johannesburg%3F%22%2C%22content%22%3A%22%3Cimg%20src%3D%5C%22https%3A%2F%2Fcdn.thewire.in%2Fwp-content%2Fuploads%2F2023%2F08%2F18181342%2FScreenshot-2023-08-18-at-6.09.53.png%5C%22%3E%3Cp%3E%3Cspan%3E%3Cstrong%3ENew%20Delhi%3A%3C%2Fstrong%3E%20While%20there%20is%20interest%20in%20a%20meeting%20between%20Chinese%20President%20Xi%20Jinping%20and%20Indian%20prime%20minister%20Narendra%20Modi%2C%20such%20an%20eventuality%20hinges%20on%20which%20side%20will%20place%20a%20request%20first.%C2%A0%3C%2Fspan%3E%3C%2Fp%3E%5Cn%3Cp%3E%3Cspan%3EBesides%20the%20actual%20G-20%20summit%20in%20September%2C%20one%20of%20the%20other%20important%20spotlights%20from%20the%20Indian%20perspective%20was%20going%20to%20be%20a%20meeting%20of%20the%20host%2C%20Modi%2C%20with%20Xi.%20It%20appears%20that%20a%20substantive%20meeting%2C%20their%20first%20since%20the%20start%20of%20the%20border%20stand-off%20in%20May%202020%2C%20may%20happen%20sooner%20than%20that%2C%20if%20things%20pan%20out.%3C%2Fspan%3E%3C%2Fp%3E%5Cn%3Cp%3E%3Cspan%3EIt%20is%20learnt%20that%20there%20is%20certainly%20interest%20in%20India%20for%20a%20meeting%20to%20take%20place%20between%20the%20two%20leaders%20in%20South%20Africa.%20However%2C%20informed%20sources%20say%20the%20pressing%20issue%20now%20revolves%20around%20customary%20protocol%20%E2%80%93%20specifically%20in%20determining%20which%20side%20will%20initiate%20the%20formal%20request%20for%20the%20meeting.%3C%2Fspan%3E%3C%2Fp%3E%5Cn%3Cp%3E%3Cspan%3EWhile%20relations%20have%20gone%20into%20a%20deep%20freeze%20since%20May%202020%2C%20there%20has%20been%20several%20rounds%20of%20military%20and%20diplomatic%20talks%20between%20the%20two%20countries%2C%20which%20eventually%20led%20to%20disengagement%20at%20certain%20friction%20points.%20And%20yet%20there%20has%20been%20no%20further%20progress%20on%20the%20remaining%20points%20for%20nearly%20two%20years%2C%20which%20renders%20the%20situation%20ripe%20for%20political%20intervention.%3C%2Fspan%3E%3C%2Fp%3E%5Cn%3Cp%3E%3Cspan%3EThere%20has%20already%20been%20strong%20indication%20for%20some%20weeks%20that%20positive%20atmospherics%20were%20being%20created%20for%20a%20possible%20bilateral%20meeting%20between%20the%20two%20leaders.%3C%2Fspan%3E%3C%2Fp%3E%5Cn%3Cp%3E%3Cspan%3EThe%20%3C%2Fspan%3E%3Ca%20href%3D%5C%22https%3A%2F%2Fmea.gov.in%2Fpress-releases.htm%3Fdtl%2F37010%2FJoint%2BPress%2BRelease%2Bof%2Bthe%2B19th%2BRound%2Bof%2BIndiaChina%2BCorps%2BCommander%2BLevel%2BMeeting%5C%22%3E%3Cspan%3Ejoint%20press%20release%3C%2Fspan%3E%3C%2Fa%3E%3Cspan%3E%20issued%20earlier%20this%20week%20had%20signalled%20this%20mood.%20Ranging%20from%20%E2%80%9Cpositive%E2%80%9D%20to%20%E2%80%9Cforward-looking%E2%80%9D%2C%20the%20common%20readout%20of%20the%20Indian%20and%20Chinese%20Corp%20commanders%E2%80%99%20meeting%20last%20weekend%20had%20a%20high%20concentration%20of%20optimistic-sounding%20descriptors%20about%20the%20discussions%20on%20the%20continuing%20stand-off%20at%20eastern%20Ladakh.%3C%2Fspan%3E%3C%2Fp%3E%5Cn%3Cp%3E%3Cspan%3EThere%20have%20been%20%3C%2Fspan%3E%3Ca%20href%3D%5C%22http%3A%2F%2Feng.chinamil.com.cn%2FCHINA_209163%2FTopStories_209189%2F10207209.html%5C%22%3E%3Cspan%3Eother%3C%2Fspan%3E%3C%2Fa%3E%20%3Ca%20href%3D%5C%22https%3A%2F%2Fwww.mea.gov.in%2Fpress-releases.htm%3Fdtl%2F35496%2FJoint%2BPress%2BRelease%2Bof%2Bthe%2B16th%2BRound%2Bof%2BIndiaChina%2BCorps%2BCommander%2BLevel%2BMeeting%5C%22%3E%3Cspan%3Ejoint%3C%2Fspan%3E%3C%2Fa%3E%20%3Ca%20href%3D%5C%22https%3A%2F%2Fpib.gov.in%2FPressReleseDetailm.aspx%3FPRID%3D1789701%5C%22%3E%3Cspan%3Epress%20releases%3C%2Fspan%3E%3C%2Fa%3E%3Cspan%3E%20after%20military%20talks%20in%20the%20last%20three%20years.%20However%2C%20even%20those%20releases%20did%20not%20contain%20as%20many%20affirmative%20words%20and%20phrases%20as%20there%20were%20in%20the%20most%20recent%20document.%3C%2Fspan%3E%3C%2Fp%3E%5Cn%3Cp%3E%3Cspan%3EChina%E2%80%99s%20top%20diplomat%20Wang%20Yi%20had%20already%20held%20two%20rounds%20of%20meeting%20with%20Indian%20interlocutors%2C%20external%20affairs%20minister%20S.%20Jaishankar%20and%20National%20Security%20Advisor%20Ajit%20Doval.%C2%A0%3C%2Fspan%3E%3C%2Fp%3E%5Cn%3Cp%3E%3Cspan%3EAfter%20the%20Doval-Wang%20meeting%2C%20the%20Chinese%20readout%20stated%20that%20there%20had%20been%20exchange%20of%20remarks%20between%20the%20top%20Indian%20and%20Chinese%20leaders%20at%20the%20G-20%20dinner%20summit%20in%20Bali.%20It%20was%20a%20previously%20unreported%20conversation%2C%20with%20the%20Indian%20side%20having%20only%20mentioned%20that%20there%20was%20an%20%3C%2Fspan%3E%3Ca%20href%3D%5C%22https%3A%2F%2Fmea.gov.in%2Fmedia-briefings.htm%3Fdtl%2F35898%2FTranscript_of_Special_Briefing_by_Foreign_Secretary_on_the_Visit_of_the_Prime_Minister_to_Indonesia_for_G20_Summit_November_16_2022%5C%22%3E%3Cspan%3Eexchange%20of%20courtesies%3C%2Fspan%3E%3C%2Fa%3E%3Cspan%3E.%3C%2Fspan%3E%3C%2Fp%3E%5Cn%3Cp%3E%3Cspan%3EWhen%20Indian%20media%20asked%20for%20clarification%2C%20New%20Delhi%20did%20not%20dismiss%20the%20Chinese%20version%2C%20but%20rather%20seemed%20to%20endorse%20it%20to%20an%20extent.%20This%20was%20a%20surprise%20to%20most%20observers%20who%20are%20aware%20of%20the%20MEA%E2%80%99s%20usual%20template%20of%20available%20replies.%20%3C%2Fspan%3E%3Ca%20href%3D%5C%22https%3A%2F%2Fthewire.in%2Fdiplomacy%2Feight-months-later-india-says-modi-xi-did-talk-about-stabilising-ties-at-bali-encounter%5C%22%3E%3Cspan%3EThe%20spokesperson%E2%80%99s%20implicit%20acknowledgment%3C%2Fspan%3E%3C%2Fa%3E%3Cspan%3E%20that%20the%20complete%20details%20had%20not%20been%20furnished%20eight%20months%20earlier%20came%20as%20a%20surprise.%3C%2Fspan%3E%3C%2Fp%3E%5Cn%3Cp%3E%3Cspan%3ENext%20week%2C%20the%20leaders%20of%20the%20bloc%20of%20five%20emerging%20economies%20will%20be%20meeting%20physically%20for%20their%20first%20summit%20since%202019.%20While%20the%20Russian%20president%20Vladimir%20Putin%20will%20not%20attend%20due%20to%20the%20%3Ca%20href%3D%5C%22https%3A%2F%2Fwww.icc-cpi.int%2Fnews%2Fsituation-ukraine-icc-judges-issue-arrest-warrants-against-vladimir-vladimirovich-putin-and%5C%22%3EInternational%20Criminal%20Court%E2%80%99s%20arrest%20warrant%3C%2Fa%3E%2C%20the%20Chinese%20foreign%20ministry%20confirmed%20today%2C%20August%2018%2C%20that%20Xi%20Jinping%20would%20travel%20to%20South%20Africa%20for%20a%20four-day%20visit.%20The%20foreign%20trip%2C%20from%20April%2021%20to%2024%2C%20is%20relatively%20long%20by%20Chinese%20standards%20and%20is%20going%20to%20include%20both%20a%20BRICS%20summit%20and%20a%20bilateral%20state%20visit.%3C%2Fspan%3E%3C%2Fp%3E%5Cn%3Cp%3E%3Cspan%3EAs%20per%20current%20schedule%2C%20Modi%20and%20his%20entourage%20will%20reach%20South%20Africa%20on%20August%2022%2C%20in%20the%20evening%20according%20to%20local%20time.%20He%20will%20attend%20the%20informal%20meet%20for%20participating%20leaders%20after%20arrival.%20The%20main%20BRICS%20summit%20will%20be%20held%20on%20August%2023%2C%20with%20the%20next%20day%20reserved%20for%20the%20BRICS%20outreach%20sessions.%20The%20Indian%20PM%20will%20depart%20for%20New%20Delhi%20on%20Thursday%20evening.%3C%2Fspan%3E%3C%2Fp%3E%5Cn%3Cp%3E%3Cspan%3EEven%20though%20South%20Africa%20has%20invited%20many%20African%20leaders%20as%20special%20invitees%2C%20it%20is%20understood%20there%20is%20enough%20time%20in%20the%20schedule%20for%20the%20Indian%20PM%20to%20have%20a%20substantive%20bilateral%20meeting%20with%20the%20Chinese%20leader.%20As%20usual%2C%20the%20dilemma%20%E2%80%93%20a%20common%20one%20for%20Indian%20diplomats%20faced%20with%20a%20potential%20meeting%20with%20Chinese%20or%20Pakistani%20leadership%20%E2%80%93%20centres%20on%20who%20makes%20the%20first%20request.%3C%2Fspan%3E%3C%2Fp%3E%22%2C%22published%22%3A1692362735000%2C%22visual%22%3A%22https%3A%2F%2Fcdn.thewire.in%2Fwp-content%2Fuploads%2F2023%2F08%2F18181342%2FScreenshot-2023-08-18-at-6.09.53.png%22%2C%22originID%22%