C%22canonicalUrl%22%3A%22https%3A%2F%2Fvariety.com%2F2023%2Fbiz%2Fglobal%2Fthe-little-mermaid-disney-sandcastle-pictures-sued-injury-1235699469%2F%22%2C%22cdnAmpUrl%22%3A%22https%3A%2F%2Fvariety-com.cdn.ampproject.org%2Fc%2Fs%2Fvariety.com%2F2023%2Fbiz%2Fglobal%2Fthe-little-mermaid-disney-sandcastle-pictures-sued-injury-1235699469%2Famp%2F%22%2C%22ampUrl%22%3A%22https%3A%2F%2Fvariety.com%2F2023%2Fbiz%2Fglobal%2Fthe-little-mermaid-disney-sandcastle-pictures-sued-injury-1235699469%2Famp%2F%22%7D%2C%7B%22title%22%3A%22Delhi%20Riots%3A%20Court%20Discharges%203%20Men%2C%20Raises%20Suspicion%20of%20'Manipulated%20Evidence'%20by%20Police%22%2C%22content%22%3A%22%3Cimg%20src%3D%5C%22https%3A%2F%2Fcdn.thewire.in%2Fwp-content%2Fuploads%2F2020%2F09%2F14122931%2FDelhi-riots.jpg%5C%22%3E%3Cp%3E%3Cstrong%3ENew%20Delhi%3A%20%3C%2Fstrong%3EA%20Delhi%20court%20has%20discharged%20three%20men%20in%20a%20case%20related%20to%20the%202020%20North-East%20Delhi%20riots%2C%20expressing%20suspicion%20that%20the%20investigating%20officer%20of%20the%20Delhi%20Police%20%E2%80%9Cmanipulated%20evidence%E2%80%9D%20and%20filed%20chargesheets%20in%20a%20%E2%80%9Cpredetermined%20and%20mechanical%20manner%E2%80%9D.%3C%2Fp%3E%5Cn%3Cp%3EThe%20judge%20has%20referred%20the%20matter%20back%20to%20the%20Delhi%20Police%20for%20an%20assessment%20of%20the%20investigation%20and%20to%20bring%20the%20complaints%20to%20a%20legal%20and%20logical%20end.%3C%2Fp%3E%5Cn%3Cp%3EThe%20three%20individuals%20%E2%80%93%20Akil%20Ahmad%20alias%20Papad%2C%20Rahish%20Khan%2C%20and%20Irshad%20%E2%80%93%20were%20accused%20of%20rioting%2C%20being%20part%20of%20an%20unlawful%20assembly%2C%20and%20committing%20vandalism%20during%20the%20riots.%3C%2Fp%3E%5Cn%3Cp%3EAccording%20to%20%3Ca%20href%3D%5C%22https%3A%2F%2Fwww.livelaw.in%2Fnews-updates%2Fdelhi-court-delhi-riots-delhi-police-manipulating-evidence-chargesheets-predetermined-manner-discharges-235493%5C%22%3E%3Cem%3ELiveLaw%3C%2Fem%3E%3C%2Fa%3E%2C%20the%20court%20found%20inconsistencies%20in%20the%20chargesheets%20and%20subsequent%20statements%2C%20suggesting%20an%20attempt%20to%20cover%20up%20flaws%20in%20the%20prosecution%E2%80%99s%20case.%3Cstrong%3E%3Cbr%3E%5Cn%3C%2Fstrong%3E%3C%2Fp%3E%5Cn%3Cp%3EA%20first%20information%20report%20(FIR%2071%2F2020)%20was%20registered%20at%20Dayalpur%20police%20station%20on%20the%20basis%20of%20a%20rukka%20prepared%20by%20an%20Assistant%20Sub-Inspector%20on%20February%2028%2C%202020.%20(Rukka%20is%20just%20a%20complaint%20copy%20from%20which%20the%20contents%20are%20taken%20for%20filing%20FIRs.)%3C%2Fp%3E%5Cn%3Cp%3ELater%2C%20the%20Investigating%20Officer%20clubbed%20several%20complaints%20made%20by%20Farooq%20Ahmad%2C%20Shahbaz%20Malik%2C%20Nadeem%20Farooq%20and%20Jai%20Shankar%20Sharma%20in%20the%20case%2C%20%3Cem%3ELiveLaw%3C%2Fem%3E%20said.%3C%2Fp%3E%5Cn%3Cp%3EA%20chargesheet%20was%20filed%20against%20the%20three%20persons%20on%20July%2014%2C%202020%2C%20and%20cognisance%20of%20the%20same%20was%20taken%20on%20December%209%2C%202020.%3C%2Fp%3E%5Cn%3Cp%3EThereafter%2C%20two%20supplementary%20chargesheets%20were%20filed%20on%20February%2015%2C%202022%2C%20and%20February%2016%20this%20year%2C%20along%20with%20certain%20documents%20and%20fresh%20statements.%3C%2Fp%3E%5Cn%3Cp%3E%3Cins%3EAlso%20read%3A%20%3Ca%20href%3D%5C%22https%3A%2F%2Fthewire.in%2Flaw%2Fpolice-witness-not-credible-callous-probe-how-the-delhi-riots-cases-have-evolved%5C%22%3E%E2%80%98Police%20Witness%20Not%20Credible%E2%80%99%2C%20%E2%80%98Callous%20Probe%E2%80%99%3A%20How%20the%20Delhi%20Riots%20Cases%20Have%20Evolved%3C%2Fa%3E%3C%2Fins%3E%3C%2Fp%3E%5Cn%3Cp%3EThe%20judge%20noted%20that%20in%20the%20first%20supplementary%20chargesheet%2C%20the%20investigating%20officer%20(IO)%20included%20three%20individuals%20as%20accused%20who%20were%20not%20mentioned%20in%20a%20constable%E2%80%99s%20statement.%3C%2Fp%3E%5Cn%3Cp%3EAdditionally%2C%20the%20court%20highlighted%20that%20until%20the%20court%20began%20questioning%20the%20timeline%20of%20events%20mentioned%20in%20the%20case%2C%20the%20IO%20consistently%20maintained%20in%20both%20the%20main%20and%20the%20first%20supplementary%20chargesheets%20that%2C%20except%20for%20one%20incident%2C%20all%20other%20reported%20incidents%20by%20various%20complainants%20occurred%20during%20the%20night%20between%20February%2024%20and%2025%2C%202020.%3C%2Fp%3E%5Cn%3Cp%3EThe%20court%20further%20noticed%20that%20when%20the%20complaints%20were%20clubbed%20together%2C%20there%20was%20no%20record%20of%20the%20police%20being%20informed%20that%20the%20same%20group%20had%20been%20involved%20in%20acts%20of%20vandalism%20and%20arson%20from%20the%20night%20before%20until%20the%20information%20was%20recorded%20on%20the%20morning%20of%20February%2025%2C%202020.%3C%2Fp%3E%5Cn%3Cp%3EFurthermore%2C%20the%20court%20said%20that%20the%20subsequent%20statements%20from%20the%20complainants%20were%20documented%20primarily%20to%20hide%20the%20gaps%20in%20the%20prosecution%E2%80%99s%20case%20and%20to%20provide%20a%20basis%20for%20charging%20the%20accused%20individuals.%20The%20court%20also%20pointed%20out%20that%20the%20investigating%20officer%20failed%20to%20present%20any%20evidence%20demonstrating%20the%20accuracy%20of%20these%20subsequent%20statements.%3C%2Fp%3E%22%2C%22published%22%3A1692351035000%2C%22visual%22%3A%22https%3A%2F%2Fcdn.thewire.in%2Fwp-content%2Fuploads%2F2020%2F09%2F14122931%2FDelhi-riots.jpg%22%2C%22originID%22%3A%22https%3A%2F%2Fthewire.in%2Flaw%2Fdelhi-riots-court-discharges-3-men-raises-suspicion-of-manipulated-evidence-by-police%22%2C%22summary%22%3A%22The%20judge%20has%20referred%20the%20matter%20back%20to%20the%20Delhi%20Police%20for%20an%20assessment%20of%20the%20investigation%20and%20to%20bring%20the%20complaints%20to%20a%20legal%20and%20logical%20end.%22%2C%22author%22%3A%22%22%2C%22engagement%22%3A13%2C%22canonicalUrl%22%3A%22https%3A%2F%2Fthewire.in%2Flaw%2Fdelhi-riots-court-discharges-3-men-raises-suspicion-of-manipulated-evidence-by-police%22%2C%22cdnAmpUrl%22%3A%22%