2C%20wrote%20in%20a%20post%20to%20internal%20forum%20Workplace%20that%20all%20employees%20%26quot%3Bassigned%20to%20an%20office%26quot%3B%20will%20be%20required%20to%20work%20from%20that%20office%20or%20otherwise%20participate%20in%20in-person%20work%20at%20least%20three%20days%20a%20week.%20Employees%20already%20approved%20for%20fully%20remote%20work%20do%20not%20have%20to%20comply%20with%20the%20three-day%20per%20week%20mandate.%3C%2Fp%3E%3Cp%3E%26quot%3BAccountability%20will%20be%20central%20to%20making%20this%20fair%20and%20effective%2C%26quot%3B%20Goler%20wrote.%3C%2Fp%3E%3Cp%3EManagers%20at%20Meta%20will%20be%20responsible%20for%20following%20up%20with%20workers%20on%20a%20monthly%20basis%2C%20making%20sure%20they%20are%20complying%20with%20RTO.%20Workers%20may%20be%20disciplined%20or%20even%20lose%20their%20jobs%20if%20they%20repeatedly%20fail%20to%20comply.%3C%2Fp%3E%3Cp%3E%26quot%3BManagers%20will%20review%20badge%20and%20Status%20Tool%20information%20on%20a%20monthly%20basis%20and%20follow%20up%20with%20those%20who%20didn't%20meet%20the%20requirement%2C%20subject%20to%20local%20law%20and%20works%20council%20requirements%2C%26quot%3B%20Goler%20wrote.%20%26quot%3BAs%20with%20other%20company%20policies%2C%20repeated%20violations%20may%20result%20in%20disciplinary%20action%2C%20up%20to%20and%20including%20a%20performance%20rating%20drop%20and%2C%20ultimately%2C%20termination%20if%20not%20addressed.%26quot%3B%3C%2Fp%3E%3Cp%3EA%20spokesman%20for%20Meta%20said%2C%20%26quot%3BWe%20believe%20that%20distributed%20work%20will%20continue%20to%20be%20important%20in%20the%20future%2C%20particularly%20as%20our%20technology%20improves.%26quot%3B%3C%2Fp%3E%3Cp%3E%26quot%3BIn%20the%20near-term%2C%20our%20in-person%20focus%20is%20designed%20to%20support%20a%20strong%2C%20valuable%20experience%20for%20our%20people%20who%20have%20chosen%20to%20work%20from%20the%20office%2C%20and%20we're%20being%20thoughtful%20and%20intentional%20about%20where%20we%20invest%20in%20remote%20work%2C%26quot%3B%20he%20added.%3C%2Fp%3E%3Cp%3EMeta%20%3Ca%20href%3D%5C%22https%3A%2F%2Fwww.businessinsider.com%2Fmeta-requiring-employees-come-to-the-office-3-days-week-2023-6%5C%22%3Efirst%20informed%3C%2Fa%3E%20employees%20of%20its%20RTO%20efforts%20in%20June%2C%20saying%20that%20beginning%20after%20the%20Labor%20Day%20holiday%2C%20people%20who%20were%20hired%20to%20work%20in%20an%20office%20should%20return%20at%20least%20part%20of%20the%20week.%3C%2Fp%3E%3Cp%3EThe%20internal%20announcement%20came%20after%20CEO%20Mark%20Zuckerberg%20began%20to%20publicly%20and%20internally%20praise%20the%20benefits%20of%20in-office%20work.%20In%20a%20March%20memo%20announcing%20%3Ca%20data-mrf-link%3D%5C%22https%3A%2F%2Fwww.businessinsider.com%2Fmark-zuckerberg-meta-layoffs-second-round-job-cuts-2023-3%5C%22%20rel%3D%5C%22%5C%22%20data-uri%3D%5C%22385c823d1b266472c19537be5cba0801%5C%22%20data-analytics-post-depth%3D%5C%2280%5C%22%20href%3D%5C%22https%3A%2F%2Fwww.businessinsider.com%2Fmark-zuckerberg-meta-layoffs-second-round-job-cuts-2023-3%5C%22%20data-analytics-product-module%3D%5C%22body_link%5C%22%3Ea%20layoff%20of%2010%2C000%20employees%3C%2Fa%3E%2C%20he%20%3Ca%20data-mrf-link%3D%5C%22https%3A%2F%2Fabout.fb.com%2Fnews%2F2023%2F03%2Fmark-zuckerberg-meta-year-of-efficiency%2F%5C%22%20rel%3D%5C%22noopener%20nofollow%5C%22%20data-uri%3D%5C%22b88fcfa73fe12c43ff0a1ae136bef724%5C%22%20data-analytics-post-depth%3D%5C%2280%5C%22%20href%3D%5C%22https%3A%2F%2Fabout.fb.com%2Fnews%2F2023%2F03%2Fmark-zuckerberg-meta-year-of-efficiency%2F%5C%22%20data-analytics-product-module%3D%5C%22body_link%5C%22%20target%3D%5C%22_blank%5C%22%3Ewrote%3C%2Fa%3E%C2%A0how%20a%20company%20analysis%20showed%20that%20%26quot%3Bengineers%20earlier%20in%20their%20career%20perform%20better%20on%20average%20when%20they%20work%20in-person%20with%20teammates%20at%20least%20three%20days%20a%20week.%26quot%3B%20The%20details%20of%20the%20analysis%20were%20not%20shared.%3C%2Fp%3E%3Cp%3EUnder%20the%20new%20policy%2C%20most%20new%20employees%2C%20save%20for%20those%20hired%20for%20rare%20fully-remote%20roles%2C%20will%20be%20required%20to%20work%20in%20the%20office.%20After%2018%20months%2C%20and%20with%20positive%20performance%20reviews%2C%20workers%20can%20apply%20to%20be%20fully%20remote.%20Being%20fully%20remote%20means%20Meta%20will%20not%20maintain%20desk%20space%20for%20such%20workers%2C%20who%20should%20not%20come%20to%20an%20office%20%26quot%3Bmore%20than%204%20days%20every%202%20months%2C%26quot%3B%20according%20to%20Goler's%20memo.%3C%2Fp%3E%3Cp%3EWhile%20Meta%20still%20allows%20some%20remote%20work%2C%20the%20overall%20shift%20away%20from%20it%20is%20a%20major%20departure%20from%20the%20pro-remote%20work%20stance%20it%20adopted%20early%20on%20in%20the%20pandemic.%20In%20an%20%3Ca%20data-mrf-link%3D%5C%22https%3A%2F%2Ftim.blog%2F2022%2F03%2F24%2Fmark-zuckerberg%2F%5C%22%20rel%3D%5C%22noopener%20nofollow%5C%22%20data-uri%3D%5C%22c3845b581e22edac59050e9cba41be96%5C%22%20data-analytics-post-depth%3D%5C%2280%5C%22%20href%3D%5C%22https%3A%2F%2Ftim.blog%2F2022%2F03%2F24%2Fmark-zuckerberg%2F%5C%22%20data-analytics-product-module%3D%5C%22body_link%5C%22%20target%3D%5C%22_blank%5C%22%3Einterview%20discussing%20Meta's%20long-term%20strategy%20on%20%26quot%3BThe%20Tim%20Ferris%20Show%26quot%3B%20last%20March%3C%2Fa%3E%2C%20Zuckerberg%20said%20on%20the%20podcast%20that%20he%20hoped%20to%20have%20%26quot%3B50%25%20or%20more%20of%20the%20company%26quot%3B%20working%20%26quot%3Bdistributed%20and%20working%20remotely%26quot%3B%20by%20the%20end%20of%20the%20decade.%20And%20Meta's%20own%20product%2C%20the%20Metaverse%2C%20was%20supposed%20to%20further%20usher%20in%20a%20new%20era%20of%20virtual%20remote-work%20options.%3C%2Fp%3E%3Ch2%3ERead%20the%20full%20note%20below%3A%3C%2Fh2%3E%3Cblockquote%3E%3Csection%3E%3Cp%3EFrom%3A%20Lori%20Goler%3Cbr%3EDistributed%20work%20updates%3Cbr%3ETL%3BDR%3A%3Cbr%3E%E2%80%A2%20We%20shared%20in%20June%20that%20beginning%20September%205%2C%20people%20assigned%20to%20an%20office%20will%20need%20to%20spend%20at%20least%203%20days%20per%20week%20in%20person%20to%20foster%20healthy%20relationships%20and%20strong%20collaboration.%3Cbr%3E%E2%80%A2%20Managers%20will%20hold%20their%20teams%20accountable%20to%20the%20In-Person%20Time%20Policy%20on%20a%20monthly%20basis.%20You%20won't%20need%20to%20make%20up%20in-person%20time%20when%20you're%20off%20work%20(e.g.%2C%20paid%20time%20off%2C%20sick%20time%2C%20unforeseen%20circumstances%20like%20a%20family%20emergency)%20or%20when%20you%20take%20Global%20or%20Domestic%20Travel%20Days.%3Cbr%3E%E2%80%A2%20Unless%20required%20for%20work%20reasons%2C%20remote%20workers%20should%20limit%20office%20visits%20to%20no%20more%20than%204%20days%20every%202%20months%20to%20help%20teams%20build%20predictable%20schedules%20and%20more%20consistent%20collaboration%20practices.%3Cbr%3EEveryone%20must%20keep%20the%20Status%20Tool%20updated%20with%20their%20correct%20work%20location.%3Cbr%3EAs%20we%20shared%20in%20June%2C%20beginning%20September%205%2C%20people%20assigned%20to%20an%20office%20need%20to%20spend%20at%20least%203%20days%20per%20week%20working%20in%20person%20to%20foster%20healthy%20relationships%20and%20strong%20collaboration.%20Consistency%20is%20key%20for%20teams%20to%20optimize%20how%20they%20work%20together%2C%20so%20we're%20also%20building%20more%20structure%20and%20clear%20guidelines%20around%20remote%20workers%20visiting%20the%20office.%20We're%20providing%20an%20overview%20of%20how%20we'll%20hold%20office%20workers%20accountable%20for%20the%20in-person%20time%20requirement%2C%20guidance%20and%20changes%20for%20remote%20workers%2C%20our%20approach%20to%20location%20strategy%2C%20and%20reminders%20about%20the%20office%20experience.%20More%20details%20and%20FAQs%20can%20be%20found%20on%20the%20People%20Portal.%3Cbr%3EIN-PERSON%20TIME%3Cbr%3E%E2%80%A2%20On%20September%205%2C%20the%20In-Person%20Time%20Policy%20will%20take%20effect.%20People%20assigned%20to%20an%20office%20are%20required%20to%20be%20in%20the%20office%2C%20or%20engaging%20in%20other%20in-person%20activities%20like%20meeting%20with%20clients%2C%20at%20least%203%20days%20per%20week.%20Some%20orgs%20will%20set%20a%20schedule%20of%20preferred%20in-office%20days%2C%20so%20please%20prioritize%20coming%20in%20then%20to%20make%20collaboration%20easier.%3Cbr%3E%E2%80%A2%20Accountability%20will%20be%20central%20to%20making%20this%20fair%20and%20effective.%20Managers%20will%20review%20badge%20and%20Status%20Tool%20information%20on%20a%20monthly%20basis%20and%20follow%20up%20with%20those%20who%20didn't%20meet%20the%20requirement%2C%20subject%20to%20local%20law%20and%20works%20council%20requirements.%20As%20with%20other%20company%20policies%2C%20repeated%20violations%20may%20result%20in%20disciplinary%20action%2C%20up%20to%20and%20including%20a%20Performance%40%20rating%20drop%20and%2C%20ultimately%2C%20termination%20if%20not%20addressed.%3Cbr%3E%E2%80%A2%20We%20know%20there%20will%20be%20weeks%20when%20you%20can't%20work%20in%20person%20for%203%20days%2C%20like%20if%20you%20take%20PTO%20or%20sick%20days%2C%20have%20jury%20duty%2C%20or%20when%20there%20are%20company%20holidays%20-%20you%20won't%20need%20to%20make%20up%20in-person%20time%20for%20these%20reasons.%20Unforeseen%20circumstances%2C%20such%20as%20family%20emergencies%20or%20dangerous%20commute%20conditions%2C%20will%20also%20count.%20You%20can%20continue%20to%20use%20Global%20and%20Domestic%20Travel%20Days%2C%20but%20only%2020%20combined%20Global%20or%20Domestic%20Travel%20Days%20would%20count%20towards%20your%20in-person%20time%20for%20the%20year.%20We%20trust%20everyone%20to%20use%20good%20judgment%20and%20act%20in%20the%20spirit%20of%20the%20policy%2C%20and%20will%20address%20outliers%20as%20needed.%20REMOTE%20WORK%3Cbr%3EOffice%20visits%3A%3C%2Fp%3E%3Cp%3E%E2%80%A2%20Remote%20work%20is%20for%20people%20who%20are%20committed%20to%20working%20from%20home%2C%20and%20isn't%20intended%20for%20those%20who%20want%20to%20spend%20regular%20time%20in%20the%20office.%20To%20help%20teams%20build%20predictable%20collaboration%20practices%2C%20we're%20asking%20remote%20workers%20not%20to%20visit%20the%20office%20more%20than%204%20days%20every%202%20months-%20unless%20there's%20a%20clear%20business%20reason%20(team%20onsite%2C%20required%20in-%20person%20meetings)%20or%20to%20attend%20Meta-sponsored%20events%20like%20Company%20All%20Hands%2C%20Metamate%20Meetups%2C%20or%20Hackathons.%3Cbr%3E%E2%80%A2%20Managers%20will%20review%20this%20monthly%2C%20subject%20to%20local%20law%20and%20works%20council%20requirements%2C%20and%20remote%20workers%20who%20consistently%20exceed%20the%20threshold%20will%20be%20required%20to%20transfer%20to%20an%20office%20and%20meet%20the%20minimum%203%20days%2Fweek%20in-person%20requirement.%3Cbr%3ERemote%20applications%3A%3Cbr%3E%E2%80%A2%20We're%20moving%20to%20a%20monthly%20review%20cycle%20for%20remote%20work%20applications%20by%20org%20leaders%20so%20they%20can%20fully%20assess%20and%20understand%20the%20impact%20of%20these%20requests%20on%20their%20organizations%20and%20sites%20as%20they%20implement%20their%20org-specific%20location%20strategy.%20Cross-border%20remote%20requests%20are%20still%20on%20hold%20until%20Q4.%3Cbr%3E%E2%80%A2%20Applications%20submitted%20from%20today%20through%20the%20end%20of%20September%20will%20be%20reviewed%20by%20the%20end%20of%20October%2C%20and%20monthly%20after%20that.%20Remote%20applications%20submitted%20before%20August%2017%20will%20move%20forward%20pending%20manager%20approval.%3Cbr%3ESTATUS%20TOOL%3Cbr%3E%E2%80%A2%20Everyone%20-%20both%20office%20and%20remote%20workers%20-%20must%20keep%20the%20Status%20Tool%20updated%20with%20your%20work%20location%2C%20ideally%202%20weeks%20in%20advance.%20This%20makes%20it%20easier%20to%20coordinate%20time%20with%20your%20team%2C%20lets%20Calendar%20manage%20your%20meeting%20rooms%2C%20helps%20Facilities%20plan%20effectively%2C%20allows%20Meta%20to%20withhold%20your%20taxes%20accurately%2C%20and%20